What is Lead Generation and Why Does it Matter?
Lead generation is the process of attracting and identifying potential customers, or "leads," who are interested in your products or services. This is a crucial step in the sales funnel, as without leads, there’s no one to engage with, nurture, or ultimately convert into paying customers.

A robust lead generation strategy enables businesses to connect with the right audience, build lasting relationships, and drive revenue growth. However, effective lead generation goes beyond just collecting names and email addresses. It involves identifying and engaging prospects who have a genuine interest in what you offer and are likely to convert into loyal customers. For B2B companies, this means targeting decision-makers and influencers within the right organizations, in the right industries, and at the right time.

